org.openimaj.ml.clustering.random

Class RandomByteClusterer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.ml.clustering.random.RandomByteClusterer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Clusterer<byte[][]>, SpatialClusterer<ByteCentroidsResult,byte[]>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RandomSetByteClusterer

    public class RandomByteClusterer
extends Object
implements SpatialClusterer<ByteCentroidsResult,byte[]>
    A simple (yet apparently quite effective in high dimensions) clustering technique trained used randomly sampled data points. A configurable number of data points are selected from the training data to represent the centroids.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk), Sina Samangooei (ss@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

      • RandomByteClusterer

        public RandomByteClusterer(int M)
        Creates a new random byte cluster used to create centroids with data containing M elements. The number of clusters will be equal to the number of data points provided in training.
        Parameters:
        M - number of elements in each data vector

        public ByteCentroidsResult cluster(byte[][] data)
        Selects K elements from the provided data as the centroids of the clusters. If K is -1 all provided data points will be selected. It is not guaranteed that the same data point will not be selected many times.
